      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COME ON LARRY (3) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by a neck at Ballarat in a handy 25.30 beating She's Saintly. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. MR. BLUEY LEE (7) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (25.76) last time in a Grade 5 at Ballarat. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. PAW NEVADA (1) was below best last time at Shepparton (22.67) in a Grade 4/5, finishing a 5.5 lengths fifth. Has already won two times from this draw. Suited here and expected to run well. DASHING DONNA (2) hit the frame here last start so don't underestimate.",
